DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The ppaasssswwdd command computes the hash of a password typed
       at run-time or the hash of each password in a list.  The
       password list is taken from the named file for option --iinn
       ffiillee, from stdin for option --ssttddiinn, and from the command
       line otherwise.  The Unix standard algorithm ccrryypptt and the
       MD5-based BSD password algorithm 11 and its Apache variant
       aapprr11 are available.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --ccrryypptt
           Use the ccrryypptt algorithm (default).

       --11  Use the MD5 based BSD password algorithm 11.

       --aapprr11
           Use the aapprr11 algorithm (Apache variant of the BSD
           algorithm).

       --ssaalltt string
           Use the specified salt.

       --iinn file
           Read passwords from file.

       --ssttddiinn
           Read passwords from ssttddiinn.

       --qquuiieett
           Don't output warnings when passwords given at the
           command line are truncated.

       --ttaabbllee
           In the output list, prepend the cleartext password and
           a TAB character to each password hash.

